For mRNA lifetime, we used two pairs of wild-type and littermate knockout mice for the lifetime experiment. The procedure was adapted from the previous report15. Briefly, actinomycinD was added to 5 μg/ml at 6, 3, and 0 h before collection. The total RNA was purified by TRIzol reagent. Before construction of the library with Tru-seq mRNA sample preparation kit (Illumina), ERCC RNA spike-in control (Ambion) was added to each sample proportional to the total RNA according to the instructions. The degradation rate of RNA k was estimated by\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
